\begin{align*}
\frac{f}{3} + 1 &= \frac{d}{3}, \\
f^2 &= d^2.
\end{align*}From the first equation, $d - f = 3.$  Since $f^2 = d^2,$ $f = d$ or $f = -d.$  We cannot have $f = d,$ so $f = -d.$  Then $2d = 3,$ so $d = \frac{3}{2}.$

